    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is an Open Format deck, designed for fun purposes only. It contains all the Free Peoples cards that are banned in the Standard format. The Shadow is a Vida Moria, and contains 3 copies of Nertea :). It also contains 4 Free peoples cultures, frimbazel the Chief Counselor. <br />
Strategy of the deck is going for the shadow kill. The fellowship draws cards via Gandalf/Elrond/Ottar/Foul Creation combo, thus setting up shadow hand. The Fellowship also chokes (No Stranger, Bill the Pony & Aragorn HttWC) , so that the opponent&#39;s fellowship has a hard time setting up, espercially after the Golden Hall hits them.<br />
Bid 3, go second if you win the bid. If the opponent plays Moria (that is, if you see the tower of cards at the opponent&#39;s side) you can go first, as there is enough condition removal, and Boromir with the Horn effectivelly disables the swarming capabilities of Moria. Move site by site, never run. Once Boromir gets the Horn, you can sacrifice your numerous allies if the things get tough.<br />
Use your Foul Creations indiscriminately, and if you manage to discard Grima, CC treat yourself (and everybody watching the game if you feel like it) with a drink.<br />
This deck has seen some casual play and I have even managed to win quite a few games with this deck.<br />
Please contact me if you have the foils needed to make this deck all-foil and are interested in the exchange.<br />
Have fun!  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
